					<component contextConductionInd="true" typeCode="COMP">
						<npfitlc:contentId extension="COCD_TP146061UK02#Section1" root="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.16"/>
						<COCD_TP146061UK02.Section1 classCode="DOCSECT" moodCode="EVN">
							<code code="DI17" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.17.243"/>
							<id root="2BA25A73-9E0F-474B-92CF-F01F3087B88B"/>
							<templateId extension="COCD_TP146061UK02#Section1" root="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.2"/>
							<text>
								Severe left-side loin pain and
								haematuria. Renal colic?
							</text>
							<title>Indication</title>
						</COCD_TP146061UK02.Section1>
					</component>
					<component contextConductionInd="true" typeCode="COMP">
						<npfitlc:contentId root="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.16" extension="COCD_TP146061UK02#Section1"/>
						<COCD_TP146061UK02.Section1 classCode="DOCSECT" moodCode="EVN">
							<code code="DI12" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.17.243"/>
							<id root="247AF3C3-1B6A-47C5-8E33-07A430AF47D7"/>
							<templateId root="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.2" extension="COCD_TP146061UK02#Section1"/>
							<text>
								The control film shows a 5mm calcified
								opacity to the left of the transverse
								process of L2 in the line of the left
								ureter. Following injection of contrast
								there was prompt excretion on the right.
								On the left there is a persistant dense
								nephrogram. There is no excretion on the
								left at 45 mins. The patient was
								transferred to ultrasound. See
								ultrasound report.
							</text>
							<title>IVU Report</title>
						</COCD_TP146061UK02.Section1>
					</component>
					<component contextConductionInd="true" typeCode="COMP">
						<npfitlc:contentId root="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.16" extension="COCD_TP146061UK02#Section1"/>
						<COCD_TP146061UK02.Section1 classCode="DOCSECT" moodCode="EVN">
							<code code="DI12" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.17.243"/>
							<id root="247AF3C3-1B6A-47C5-8E33-07A430AF47D8"/>
							<templateId root="2.16.840.1.113883.2.1.3.2.4.18.2" extension="COCD_TP146061UK02#Section1"/>
							<text>
								The right kidney is normal. The left
								kidney is enlarged and shows moderate
								hydronephrosis. There debris within the
								pelvi-calyceal system. The upper ureter
								is dilated. The appearances are
								consistant with obstruction by stone
								with possible pyonephrosis (see here).
							</text>
							<title>Ultrasound Renal Report</title>
						</COCD_TP146061UK02.Section1>
